HEADWORD: Isatis
<hw>I"sa*tis</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a kind
of plant, Gr. <?/ woad.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of herbs,
some species of which, especially the <spn>Isatis tinctoria</spn>, yield
a blue dye similar to indigo; woad.</def>⟦br⟧
